data.name: Season matches results
from
data.description: Optional parameter to specify the first match number to use to compute the result (default 1)

data.name: fromdate
data.description: Compute the table only with matches played fromdate (format mmddyyyy)

data.name: how
data.description: Return only goals scored according the how parameter. Its value can be: left, right, head or any, that is the default.

data.name: mode
data.description: Optional parameter to restrict the table compute on home or away games (default all)

data.name: page
data.description: Page result to return. Default is 1 that are results from 1 to 5 (max. value is 20).

data.name: player
data.description: Optional parameter to get goals number only for the player name specified

data.description: Optional parameter to specify the last match number to consider to compute the result (default last match number played registered on system)

description: Bundesliga Live Scores API allows to retrieve historical data as well as current season results, scorers, lineups, substitutes, events, statistics, odds and much more all with live updates, for the top professional German football league. And more features are coming...
